28/05/2003
ATHENS, Greece -- Prime Minister Costas Simitis addressed a joint meeting of the ruling PASOK party's central committee and parliamentary group on Tuesday (27 May), outlining the government's priorities until the end of its term. These include formulating Greece's position within an enlarged EU, resolving the Cyprus dispute within the framework of the UN-proposed peace plan, and reforming relations with Turkey.
In other news, the Athens newspaper <I>To Vima</I> reported Tuesday that Greece is considered among the top targets for a terrorist attack by the al-Qaeda network. Greek officials declined to comment on the report. (ANA, MPA, AFP - 27/05/03)
